  "articleSummary": "Thearticle is a practical guide for front‑end developers who want to speed up UI work without spending money on design assets. It curates free, open‑source or freemium resources—React and Tailwind component libraries (Aceternity UI, Shadcnblocks, Tailark), AI‑focused UI kits, icon sets (Lucide, Simple Icons), illustration packs, font repositories (Fontsource, Google Fonts), color‑and‑contrast tools (Coolors, WebAIM), animation libraries (GSAP, Anime.js), and lightweight design editors (Photopea, Penpot). The tone is tutorial‑like, offering a “start here” checklist and organized sections that act as a toolbox rather than a critique, and it repeatedly frames the resources as “ready‑made blocks” that let developers ship faster instead of reinventing common patterns. The intended audience is developers building web or app interfaces who need polished design components without a design team or budget.",
